owl:Ontology.terms:title: The Industrial Dataspace Information Model
owl:Ontology.rdfs:comment: This ontology defines classes and properties for describing participants, infrastructure, data and services of the Industrial Dataspace.
owl:Ontology.rdfs:label: IDS Information Model

owl:AnnotationProperty.terms:description: Spatial topic and spatial applicability may be a named place or a location specified by its geographic coordinates. Temporal topic may be a named period, date, or date range. A jurisdiction may be a named administrative entity or a geographic place to which the resource applies. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Thesaurus of Geographic Names [TGN]. Where appropriate, named places or time periods can be used in preference to numeric identifiers such as sets of coordinates or date ranges.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Refers to a quality annotation. Quality annotation can be applied to any kind of resource, e.g., a dataset, a linkset, a graph, a set of triples. However, in the DQV context, this property is generally expected to be used in statements in which subjects are instances of dcat:Dataset or dcat:Distribution.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has quality annotation

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Refers to the performed quality measurements. Quality measurements can be performed to any kind of resource (e.g., a dataset, a linkset, a graph, a set of triples). However, in the DQV context, this property is generally expected to be used in statements in which subjects are instances of dcat:Dataset or dcat:Distribution.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has quality measurement

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Refers to a grouping of quality information such as certificates, policies, measurements and annotations as a named graph. Quality information represented in such a grouping can pertain to any kind of resource (e.g., a dataset, a linkset, a graph, a set of triples). However, in the DQV context, this property is generally expected to be used in statements in which subjects are instances of dcat:Dataset or dcat:Distribution.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has quality metadata

owl:ObjectProperty.vann:usageNote: Categories are meant to systematically organize dimensions. The Data Quality Vocabulary defines no specific cardinality constraints for dqv:inCategory, since distinct quality frameworks might have different perspectives over a dimension. A dimension may therefore be associated to more than one category. However, those who define new quality metrics should try to avoid this as much as possible and assign only one category to the dimensions they define.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Represents the category a dimension is grouped in.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: in category

owl:ObjectProperty.vann:usageNote: Dimensions are meant to systematically organize metrics, quality certificates and quality annotations. The Data Quality Vocabulary defines no specific cardinality constraints for dqv:inDimension, since distinct quality frameworks might have different perspectives over a metric. A metric may therefore be associated to more than one dimension. However, those who define new quality metrics should try to avoid this as much as possible and assign only one dimension to the metrics they define. More than one dimension can be indicated for each quality annotation or certificate.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Represents the dimensions a quality metric, certificate and annotation allow a measurement of.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: in dimension

owl:Class.terms:description: A collection is described as a group; its parts may also be separately described.

owl:Class.terms:description: Metadata for an event provides descriptive information that is the basis for discovery of the purpose, location, duration, and responsible agents associated with an event. Examples include an exhibition, webcast, conference, workshop, open day, performance, battle, trial, wedding, tea party, conflagration.
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A non-persistent, time-based occurrence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Event

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Image

owl:Class.terms:description: Examples include forms on Web pages, applets, multimedia learning objects, chat services, or virtual reality environments.
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A resource requiring interaction from the user to be understood, executed, or experienced.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Interactive Resource

owl:Class.terms:description: Examples include animations, movies, television programs, videos, zoetropes, or visual output from a simulation. Instances of the type Moving Image must also be describable as instances of the broader type Image.
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A series of visual representations imparting an impression of motion when shown in succession.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Moving Image

owl:Class.terms:description: Note that digital representations of, or surrogates for, these objects should use Image, Text or one of the other types.
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An inanimate, three-dimensional object or substance.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Physical Object

owl:Class.terms:description: Examples include a photocopying service, a banking service, an authentication service, interlibrary loans, a Z39.50 or Web server.
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A system that provides one or more functions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Service

owl:Class.terms:description: Examples include a C source file, MS-Windows .exe executable, or Perl script.
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A computer program in source or compiled form.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Software

owl:Class.terms:description: Examples include a music playback file format, an audio compact disc, and recorded speech or sounds.
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A resource primarily intended to be heard.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sound

owl:Class.terms:description: Examples include paintings, drawings, graphic designs, plans and maps. Recommended best practice is to assign the type Text to images of textual materials. Instances of the type Still Image must also be describable as instances of the broader type Image.
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A static visual representation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Still Image

owl:Class.terms:description: Examples include books, letters, dissertations, poems, newspapers, articles, archives of mailing lists. Note that facsimiles or images of texts are still of the genre Text.
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A resource consisting primarily of words for reading.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Text

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents a group of quality dimensions in which a common type of information is used as quality indicator.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Category

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents criteria relevant for assessing quality. Each quality dimension must have one or more metric to measure it. A dimension is linked with a category using the dqv:inCategory property.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Dimension

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents a standard to measure a quality dimension. An observation (instance of dqv:QualityMeasurement) assigns a value in a given unit to a Metric.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Metric

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents quality annotations, including ratings, quality certificates or feedback that can be associated to datasets or distributions. Quality annotations must have one oa:motivatedBy statement with an instance of oa:Motivation (and skos:Concept) that reflects a quality assessment purpose. We define this instance as dqv:qualityAssessment.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Quality Annotation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An annotation that associates a resource (especially, a dataset or a distribution) to another resource (for example, a document) that certifies the resource's quality according to a set of quality assessment rules.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Quality Certificate

owl:Class.vann:usageNote: The unit of measure in quality measurement should be specified through the property sdmx-attribute:unitMeasure as recommended by RDF Data Cube. The Ontology of units of Measure (OM) by Rijgersberg Et Al provides a list of HTTP dereferenceable unit of measures, which can be exploited as values for sdmx-attribute:unitMeasure.
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents the evaluation of a given dataset (or dataset distribution) against a specific quality metric.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Quality Measurement

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents a dataset of quality measurements, evaluations of one or more datasets (or dataset distributions) against specific quality metrics.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Quality Measurement Dataset

owl:Class.vann:usageNote: QualityMetadata containers do not necessary include all types of quality statements DQV can support. Implementers decide the granularity of containment. In the current version of DQV, we also leave open the choice of the containment technique. Implementers can use (RDF) graph containment. They may also use an appropriate property of their choice — for example (a subproperty of) dcterms:hasPart — to link instances of dqv:QualityMetadata with instances of other DQV classes.
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents quality metadata, it is defined to group quality certificates, policies, measurements and annotations under a named graph.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Quality Metadata

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents a policy or agreement that is chiefly governed by data quality concerns.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Quality Policy

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents feedback that users have on the quality of datasets or distributions. Besides dqv:qualityAssessment, which is the motivation required by all quality annotations, one of the predefined instances of oa:Motivation should be indicated as motivation to distinguish among the different kinds of feedback, e.g., classifications, questions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: User Quality feedback

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message requesting an access token. This is intended for point-to-point communication with, e.g., Brokers.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Access Token Request

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Response to an access token request, intended for point-to-point communication.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Access Token Response

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Internal or external Agent interacting with the Industrial Data Space, not necessarily an IDS Participant.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Agent

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Secure platform for distributing Data Apps.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: App Store

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Instance of a Representation materialized at a partiuclar version and point in time. Possesses characteristics like file name, size, creation date etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Artifact

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message that follows up a RetrieveArtifact Message and contains the Artifact's data in the payload section.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Artifact Response

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Terminal data nodes, i.e. an atomic, possibly typed scalars.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Atomic data

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Content intended for auditive perception, requires an audio output device (i.e. a loudspeaker) to present the contents.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Audio

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Audio representation
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Audio

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource (at least partially) comprising audio content.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Audio Resource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of authentication standards that may be supported by Connectors.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: AuthStandard

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Implementation of the Connector specification providing only restricted security capabilities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Base Connector

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of binary operators.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: BinaryOperator

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Query command intended to be consumed by a Broker.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Broker Query Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class of scopes that may limit the space of broker query results.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RejectionReason

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: e.g. Paypal, Visa Card
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Cash machine

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The Clearing House provides clearing and settlement services B2B interactions within the International Data Spaces.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Clearing House

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Group of elements supporting particular access operations based on the concrete subclass.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Collection

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Representation of a Collection, i.e. a Map or List of elements.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Collection representation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource comprising a set of named (Map) or ordered (List) elements.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Collection resource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Process and result of certifying a software component/servivce in order to become a certified part of the International Data Space infrastructure.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Component Certification

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Level of a Component Certification
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Component Certification Level

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource comprising multiple Digital Contents.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Composite Resource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Event notifying the recipient(s) about the availability of a new connector. The payload of the message must contain the new connector's self-description.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Connector Available Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Event notifying the recipient(s) about a connector's configuration change. The payload of the message must contain the updated connector's self-description.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Connector Configuration Change Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Event notifying the recipient(s) that a connector will be temporarily unavailable and most likely be available again in the future.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Connector Temporarlily Unavailable Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Event notifying the recipient(s) that a connector will be unavailable and never be available again.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Connector Unavailable Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of Constraints that restrict a Rule.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Constraint

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Operation for receiving data via the operation’s input parameter(s) from the Data Provider to the Data Consumer.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Consume content operation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Container composed of multiple (individually defined) parts.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Container

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Container representation, i.e. of a (compressed) archive.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Container representation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message containing a contract with resource access modalities on which two parties have agreed.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Contract Agreement Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Contract issued by the Data Provider offering the usage of a Resource at particular conditions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Contract offer

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message containing a offered content contract (as offered by the data provider to the data consumer) in the associated payload (which is an instance of ContractOffer).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Contract Offer Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message indicating rejection of a contract.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Contract Rejection Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Contract issued by the Data Consumer requesting the usage of a Resource at particular conditions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Contract request

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Activity with the goal to generate or produce an entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: CreationActivity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A selection of custom media types to be used for data published on the IDS when no IANA type is available.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Custom Media Type

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Custom or generic (semi)structured data intended for machine processing, i.e. atomic values or arrangements of data fields (optionally defined by a schema).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Data

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Script code, algorithm or any other kind of interpreted software.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DataApp Asset

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Add-on software extending a host Data App with a dedicated capability. The plugin depends on a particular version (range) of the host Data App which governs its integration, configuration and life-cycle.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DataApp Plugin

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Data App for a (stateless) processing of digital content according to exposed software interfaces.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: DataProcessingApp

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Physical representation of (structured) data.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Data representation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource (at least partially) comprising data content.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Data Resource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of datatypes for usage by Operation Parameters.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Data Type

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of Duties as defined in the ODRL ontology.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Duty

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Evaluation Facilities carry out the evaluation work during a certification process and issue the corresponding Certifications.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Evaluation Facility

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Rules describing the relation and delivery of fault messages, i.e. whether they are omitted, replace or follow a regular operation message.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Fault propagation rule

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The product is charged based on a selection of features (i.e. map overlays, service set etc.)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Feature-based pricing

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter holding a filter expression (matcher) used to identify a matching selection of contents.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Filter parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The product is charged on subscription base independently of the actual consumption.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Flatrate pricing

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The product is free of charge, its usage is optionally restricted by non-financial constraints.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Free use

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Model that exposes limited parts of the product at no cost, while additional parts are charged.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Freemium model

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A location identified by a geonames URL.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: GeoFeature

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter for conveying identifiers as defined by, e.g. an element collection (name/key). The identifier is unique and valid (in a defined context) regardless of the actual extent, ordering, and view (filtering).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Identifier parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The Identity Provider manages and validates the digital identity of International Data Spaces Participants.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Identity provider

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Static content intended for visual perception/interpretation, requires a display device (i.e. a screen) to present the contents.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Image

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Image representation
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Image

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource (at least partially) comprising image content.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Image Resource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter conveying the transient, positional identifier of a resource in the context of an ordered Collection. The resource index is temporarily unique and valid only with respect to the actual extent, ordering, and view (filtering) of the Collection.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Index parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Classification according to International Standard Industrial Classification (ISIC).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ISIC Industrial Classification

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A temporal entity with zero extent or duration.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Instant

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Instances of the LeftOperand class are used as the leftOperand of a Constraint.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: LeftOperand

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class of Licences to be referred to by Resources.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: License

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter indicating the number of elements retrieved or provided at once within a paginated subset (page).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Limit parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Ordered collection of elements allowing for an index-based access.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: List

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Operation used by a Data Consumer to retrieve an enumeration of Collection's contents.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: List content operation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Operation used to retrieve the enumeration of available values for an 'Identifier' Parameter type. Depending on the type of underlying Resource collection, the identifier may be a unique name (map) or a numeric index (list); the Data Consumer may use the identifier for a subsequent call to 'Read' operation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: List identifiers

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Operation exposing a list (ordered collection) of Digital Content.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: List operation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Operation used by a (potential) Data Consumer to retrieve (a dynamically generated) enumeration of input parameter values (its enumerated value domain); suitable for use cases in which the complete parameter range cannot be specified beforehand.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: List parameter values operation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Collection of elements allowing for a key based access.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Map

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Pattern governing the sequencing and cardinality of operation parameters.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Message exchange pattern

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Activity that sustainably modifies the managed entity, resulting in a new version.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ModificationActivity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Entity that is identifiable within a context by means of a name.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Named

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter indicating the absolute offset (number of data elements to skip) within an ordered data Collection. Negative values are bounded at Collections's end (reverse) index.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Offset parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Opaque, not further specified type of custom, binary content.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Opaque content

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message indicating that the result of a former InvokeOperation message is available. May transfer the result data in its associated payload section.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Operation Result Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter conveying the transient, positional identifier of a content page within a server-defined pagination.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Page index parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter conveying a relative reference to a content page within a server-defined pagination.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Page reference parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Whenever a Participant has been successfully certified by the Certification Body, the Identity Provider can use this message to notify Infrastructure Components.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Participant Certificate Granted Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Event notifying the recipient(s) that a Participant is temporarily no more certified.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Participant Certificate Suspended Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates that a (previously certified) Participant is no more certified. This could happen, for instance, if the Certification Body revokes a granted certificate or if the certificate just expires.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Participant Certificate Unavailable Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Process and result of certifying an interested party in order to become a certified member of the International Data Space.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Participant Certification

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Level of a Participant Certification
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Participant Certification Level

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Event notifying the recipient(s) that information describing this Participant has changed. This event is mainly intended for information describing the Participant that is NOT a direct subject of the certification process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Participant Information Changed Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Payment method requiring a contract allowing the product provider to charge the subscriber.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Post-paid payment

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: e.g. prepaid SIM
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Pre-paid payment

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Operation for processing of digital content via operation’s IO parameter(s).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Process content operation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of Prohibitions as defined in the ODRL ontology.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Prohibition

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Set of communication rules by which a Service implements its Interface(s) in order to become invocable.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Communication Protocol

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Operation for providing a single Resource content via an operation’s output parameter from the Data Provider to the Data Consumer.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Provide content operation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Activity with the goal to bring an entity into an operational state.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ProvisioningActivity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Public key as used in asymmetric cryptography.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Public Key

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Activity with the goal to make available an entity for public or restricted access.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PublicationActivity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The product is charged by instances of usage based on a particular metrics (byte size, number of API calls, ports etc.).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Quantity-based pricing

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class of query languages in which query strings may be formalized.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: QueryLanguage

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Rejection messages are specialized response messages that notify the sender of a message that processing of this message has failed.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Rejection Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class of reasons that might lead to issuing a Rejection message.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RejectionReason

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Activity with the goal to decommission an entity so that it can never be used anymore.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RemovalActivity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter conveying a representation of resource's principal content, contrasted to parameters mediating arbitrary data.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Resource parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Result messages are intended to annotate the results of a query command.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Result Message

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Activity with the goal to resume operation of a temporarily suspended entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ResumptionActivity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource (at least partially) comprising a Schema.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Schema Resource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Security guarantee claimed by a security profile.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Security guarantee

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Set of security guarantees claimed by a Connector. Connectors may asses their mutual technical reliability and trustworthiness by evaluating each other’s security profile.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SecurityProfile

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter holding a selector expression used to retrieve a subset of a Resource contents.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Selector parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message requesting the self-description of an Infrastructure Component.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Self Description Request

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Message containing the self-description of an Infrastructure Component.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Self Description Response

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Activity with the goal to make an entity unoperational, while retaining it and make it operational again at a later point in time.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ShutdownActivity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource comprising exactly one Digital Content.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Simple Resource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An office or other premise at which the organization is located
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Site

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Executable software (binary), interpreted program code (source) or fragments thereof. Intended purpose is an optional preprocessing (i.e. compilation, installation) and subsequnt execution/invokation of the software.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Software
owl:Class.skos:note: Term 'application' was misleading, since Mime Type of same name refers to unspecified data processed by some type of application program.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Software representation
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Software

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource (at least partially) comprising Software.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Software Resource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter indicating the keys underlying the sorting of an ordered Collection.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sort key parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class of possible order methods for collections.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sort Order

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Parameter indicating the sort direction of an ordered Collection.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sort order parameter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Regulation mandated by a standardization body or set of rules established and followed by a community (de facto Standard).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Standard

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Custom or standardized structured data
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Structure

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Payment taking on periodical rate according to underlying contract terms.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Subscription payment

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Activity with the goal to temporarily suspend operation of an entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SuspensionActivity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Data Apps that integrate sources and sinks of digital content maintained internally on Participant's premises with a Connector.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: System Adapter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A temporal interval or instant.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TemporalEntity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Informative textual content intended for reading and interpretation by humans and other intelligent agents. Comprises any digital representation of text, e.g. document and image (screenshot).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Text
owl:Class.skos:note: Text generlizes the notion of Media Type 'text' as a meaningful sequence of characters written in a set of human language(s), regardless of the formating and file type (e.g. plain, Word or PostScript).

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Representation of a textual content.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Text representation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource (at least partially) comprising textual content.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Text Resource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Hardened implementation of the Connector specification providing enhanced security capabilities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Trusted Connector

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Generic class of units used with quantifiable properties.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Unit

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Literal, inline value instantiation of a representation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Value

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Dynamic content intended for visual and auditive perception, combines requirements of image and audio Content Types, while imposing further requirements on video decoding etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Video

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Video representation
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Video

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Resource (at least partially) comprising video content.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Video Resource

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Activity with the goal to withdraw public or restrict availability of an entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: WithdrawActivity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of contraints concerning the right operand of a relation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Constraint

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Tailored view defined upon and generated from an ontology for a particular purpose.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Model view

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Abstract grouping of concepts relevant for a particular model view.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Package

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of all property validations.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PropertyValidation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The class of relation types, i.e., cardinality definitions of left and right operands of a relation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RelationType

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The set of conceptual resources specified by the Dewey Decimal Classification.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: DDC

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The set of media types specified by the Internet Assigned Numbers Authority.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: IMT

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The set of conceptual resources specified by the Library of Congress Classification.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: LCC

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The set of labeled concepts specified by the Library of Congress Subject Headings.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: LCSH

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The set of labeled concepts specified by the Medical Subject Headings.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: MeSH

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The set of conceptual resources specified by the National Library of Medicine Classification.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: NLM

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The set of places specified by the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: TGN

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The set of conceptual resources specified by the Universal Decimal Classification.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: UDC

owl:NamedIndividual.terms:description: The Data Quality Vocabulary (DQV) is seen as an extension to DCAT to cover the quality of the data, how frequently is it updated, whether it accepts user corrections, persistence commitments etc. When used by publishers, this vocabulary will foster trust in the data amongst developers.
owl:NamedIndividual.terms:title: Data Quality Vocabulary

owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: Precision is a quality dimension, which refers to the recorded level of details. It represents the exactness of a measurement or description. It is equivalent the notion of Precision from ISO 25012.

owl:NamedIndividual.vann:usageNote: Whenever DQV implementers need to extend the motivations for quality annotations, they should follow the instructions provided by the Web Annotation Data Model, and the concepts in the extension should be defined as specializations of dqv:qualityAssessment.
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: Motivation that must be specified for quality annotations.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: OAUTH2 via JWT

owl:NamedIndividual.metamodel:usage: Instances of Content Type are used to more precisely specify the type, genre or interpretation of a Digital Content.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The date (and optional time and timezone) of exercising the action of the Rule.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: dateTime

owl:NamedIndividual.metamodel:rationale: Extends ids:ListContentOperation, since filtering upon entire Digital Contents which definition still applies.

owl:NamedIndividual.metamodel:example: idsc_media:TEXT_CSV a ids:IANAMediaType; # the retrieved representation (HTML, turtle, RDF/XML) depends on content negotiation owl:sameAs <https://w3id.org/spar/mediatype/text/csv> .
owl:NamedIndividual.metamodel:usage: Definition of an ids:IANAMediaType should define individual equivalence to corresponding SPAR-Media Type.
ids:CustomMediaType is used only when no ids:IANAMediaType available.
Instances of Operation Type are used to more precisely specify the type, genre or interpretation of an Operation.
Instances of this class conform to a certain textual representation which they need to indicate via a property.

owl:NamedIndividual.metamodel:rationale: Extends ids:QueryOperation, since content selection is driven by user-provided logic and can hardly be defined at description time

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The allowed region of the consuming connector or Data App.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Absolute geo-spatial position

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: and operator
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: and

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Numeric count of executions of the action of the Rule.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: count

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Equals operator.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: equals

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Greater-than operator.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: greater

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: less

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: or operator

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Monetary amount to pay.

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The class of mutable individuals that are a potential subject to lifecycle management which may need to be tracked.

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: General class of media types (formerly known as MIME types).
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Media Type

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Metadata describing payload exchanged by interacting Connectors.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Message

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Notification that a message has been successfully processed (i.e. not ignored or rejected).
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Message Processed

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Event messages are informative and no response is expected by the sender.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Notification Message

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Building block of an Interface; describes the interaction by defining input, output and error parameters.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Operation

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Mapping of abstract operation signatures onto the concrete structures (e.g., HTTP headers or query parameters).
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: operation binding

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Enumerated types of operations expanding upon the Operation taxonomy.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Operation type

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Named slot of an interface operation i.e., an input, output or fault (exception).
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Parameter

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Expression of assigning a value to a parameter without creating an immediate reference.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Parameter assignment

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Class of Parameters grouped according to an operator.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Parameter group

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The class of operators that relate all members of a ParameterGroup.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ParameterGroupingOperator

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Stakeholder in the Industrial Data Space, assuming one or more of the predefined roles; every participant is given a unique identity by the Identity Provider.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Participant

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Model considering the type and timing of the payment (the effective financial compensation).
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Payment model

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The class of Permissions as defined in the ODRL ontology.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Permission

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The class of persons (people)
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Person

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The class of templates that describe a certain data usage policy.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Policy template

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Overall commodization model composed of options.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Commodization model

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Option of turning a Resource or Service into a product.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Commodization option

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Query commands are intended to annotate query strings in a specified query language or address a specific resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Query Command

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Reading operation considered 'safe' by not affecting the state of the provising component.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Query

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Syntactic template of a Resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Representation

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A particular instance of given representation.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Representation instance

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Notification that a request has been accepted and is being processed.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Request In Process Message

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Client-generated message initiating a communication, motivated by a certain reason and with an answer expected.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Request Message

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Resource is a single digital content or a coherent set of digital contents. Resource content is formalized in Representations and optionally materialized as Artifacts. The Resource's content is exposed via defined Interfaces at various protocol Endpoints.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Resource

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Response messages hold information about the reaction of a recipient to a formerly sent command or event. They must be correlated to this message.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Response Message

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Superclass of Permissions, Prohibitions and Duties.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Rule

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Operation provides the Data Consumer with custom fragments of the original Collection according to supplied 'Selector' Parameter. The Selector is applied to 'structured' Resource content.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Select content operation

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Operation allowing the Client to navigate list content based on index of Server-defined sections.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Server-side absolute paginating operation

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Operation allowing the Client to navigate list content by references to Server-defined sections.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Server-side relative paginating operation

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Operation allowing for sorting of an underlying List.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Sorting operation

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Anything with spatial extent, i.e. size, shape, or position, e.g., places and unique positions.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: SpatialEntity

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Endpoint exposing an Artifact.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Static Endpoint

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A token (e.g., for authorization) mediated as part of the message.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Token.

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Possible formats for (security-related) tokens.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Token format

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The operation relating to the asset for which permission is being granted.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: action

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Constraint that refines an Action.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: action refinement

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Freetext description of what has been performed by the Activity.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: activityDescription

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The recipient of the policy statement.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: assignee

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The issuer of the policy statement.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: assigner

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The URL of the authentication service that is provided by the Connector.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: authService

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: References a new artifact from an availability indication.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Available Artifact

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The basic offered contract that the contract request message refers to.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Base Contract Offer

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Reference to a Connector listed in the Broker.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: connector

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The constraint to be used for a specific rule.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: constraint

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Consumer of a Resource or Service that is the subject matter of the Contract. This party may differ from the Assignee specified by the Contract rules.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Consumer

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Reference to a Digital Content (physically or logically) included, definition of part-whole hierarchies.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: content part

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Constraint that refines a (composite) Digital Content.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: content refinement

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Standards document defining the given Digital Content. The content is assumed to conform to that Standard.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: content standard

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Reference to a Contract Offer defining the authorized use of the Resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: contract offer

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Email address for contacting the participant on a general level.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: corporateEmailAddress

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: General official homepage of the participant.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: corporateHomepage

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Correlated message, e.g. a response to a previous request.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: consumer connector

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Participant responsible for the correctness of the content offered by the InfrastructureComponent.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: curator

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: URL reference to a custom license regulating the general usage of the Resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Custom License

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Date coordinate of the instant.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: date

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Date time with a defined time zone.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: date time

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Localized) textual description of the entity.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: description

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The Duties imposed by a Permission.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: duty

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Email contact of a person.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: emailAddress

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The point in time when the Activity was ended.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: endedAt

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Holds information when an Operation has failed.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: fault

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Refers to a GeoPoint that is member of a BoundingPolygon.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: geoPoint

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Website providing additional information about a person.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: homepage

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Networked host operated by the Connector in order to serve and consume resource content and services.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: host

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Data-URL containing the software icon data according to RFC 2397.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Software icon

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Information Model version that the InfrastructureComponent is capable of reading/processing.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: inboundModelVersion

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Industry branch covered by the Participant.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: industrial classification

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Reference to an input Parameter (optionaly) used by the Operation.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: input

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Reference to an instance of given representation, i.e. inline value or file placeholder.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: instance

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Managed Entity that was the source of the modification.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: originalEntity

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Date of issuing the Message.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: issued

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The Connector which is the origin of the message.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: issuer connector

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Controlled keywords that describe the nature, purpose, or use of the content.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: keyword

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Natural language(s) used within the content.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: language

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Latitude of a GeoPoint (decimal degrees).
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: latitude

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Activity that occurs during the lifecycle of the Managed Entity.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: lifecycleActivity

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Longitude of a GeoPoint (decimal degrees).
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: longitude

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Participant responsible for technical maintenance of the InfrastructureComponent.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: maintainer

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Reference to an input Parameter required by the Operation.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: mandatoryInput

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Holds the mandatory result of an Operation.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: mandatoryOutput

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Indicates that a participant has a member which is again a participant. This is useful for defining hierarchical relations in a participant's organization as well as identifying groups of participants to capture, e.g., members of a collaboration.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: member participant

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Indicates membership of a person to an organization.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: memberPerson

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A Duty imposed by the Contract.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: obligation

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A Resource that is part of a Connector, indicating a offering (of, e.g., data).
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: offer

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Parameter assignment of the invoked operation's input parameters.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Operation Parameterization

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: References the operation to be invoked on the recipient's side.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Operation Reference

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Holds the result of an Operation.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: output

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Declares a member of a ParameterGroup.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: paramGroupMember

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Parameter which content is being assigned.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: parameter

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A Permission granted by the Contract.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: permission

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Phone number of a person.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: phoneNumber

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A Prohibition imposed by the Contract.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: prohibition

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Provider of a Resource or Service that is the subject matter of the contract. This party may differ from the Assigner specified by the Contract rules.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Provider

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The Agent for which the Mesaage is intended.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: recipient agent

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The Connector which is the recipient of the message.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: recipient connector

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Representation of the content.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: representation

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Standards document defining the given Representation (in contrast to general Resource content). The Representation is assumed to conform to that Standard.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: representation standard

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A Resource that is part of a Connector, indicating a request (of, e.g., data, software,...).
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: request

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: References an artifact in the context of a request.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Requested Artifact

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Reference to the Endpoints serving the resource's content.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: resource endpoint

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Reference to a Resource (physically or logically) included, definition of part-whole hierarchies.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: resource part

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Sample Resource instance.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sample

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Reference to a security guarantee supported by given profile.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Security guarantee

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The Agent which initiated the Message.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sender agent

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Named spatial entity covered by the Resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: spatial coverage

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The point in time when the Activity was started.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: startedAt

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Temporal period or instance covered by the content.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: temporal coverage

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Abstract or concrete concept related to or referred by the content.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: theme

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Localized) name of the entity.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: title

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The contract which is (or will be) the legal basis of the data transfer.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: transferContract

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The unit of measurement of a Constraint.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: unit

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Equivalent) variant of given Resource, e.g. a translation.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: variant

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The property a PropertyValidation targets.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: forProperty
